1
00:00:37,023 --> 00:00:38,752
Sometimes...

2
00:00:38,825 --> 00:00:42,226
Dr. Lecter and I would talk
when things got quiet enough...

3
00:00:42,295 --> 00:00:44,354
about the science courses
I was taking, and--

4
00:00:44,431 --> 00:00:45,098
Some kind of mail-order courses
in psychology, Nurse Barney?

5
00:00:45,098 --> 00:00:48,590
Some kind of mail-order courses
in psychology, Nurse Barney?

6
00:00:48,668 --> 00:00:49,930
No, sir.

7
00:00:50,003 --> 00:00:52,938
See, I don't consider
psychology a science...

8
00:00:53,006 --> 00:00:55,372
and neither did Dr. Lecter.

9
00:00:58,411 --> 00:01:02,507
Now, Barney, while you
were working at the asylum...

10
00:01:02,582 --> 00:01:03,116
you observed Clarice Starling
and Hannibal Lecter interacting.

11
00:01:03,116 --> 00:01:08,850
you observed Clarice Starling
and Hannibal Lecter interacting.

12
00:01:08,922 --> 00:01:10,514
Interacting?

13
00:01:10,590 --> 00:01:13,286
Talking to one another.

14
00:01:13,360 --> 00:01:16,227
Yes. It seemed to me that they--

15
00:01:16,296 --> 00:01:19,754
I see you're eager to justify
your consulting fee...

16
00:01:19,833 --> 00:01:23,098
but why don't we start
with what you saw...

17
00:01:23,169 --> 00:01:25,262
not what you thought about
what you saw?

18
00:01:25,338 --> 00:01:26,930
Cordell, don't be like that.

19
00:01:27,007 --> 00:01:29,703
Barney can give us his opinion.

20
00:01:29,776 --> 00:01:34,145
Barney, give us your opinion
of what you saw.

21
00:01:34,214 --> 00:01:37,377
What was it between them?

22
00:01:37,450 --> 00:01:39,179
Most of the time...

23
00:01:39,252 --> 00:01:42,221
Dr. Lecter didn't respond at all
to visitors.

24
00:01:42,288 --> 00:01:43,846
He'd just, for instance...

25
00:01:43,923 --> 00:01:46,483
open his eyes long enough
to insult some academic...

26
00:01:46,559 --> 00:01:49,585
who was there to look over him.

27
00:01:49,662 --> 00:01:52,392
With Starling,
he answered her questions.

28
00:01:52,465 --> 00:01:54,023
She interested him.

29
00:01:54,100 --> 00:01:56,432
She intrigued him.

30
00:01:56,503 --> 00:01:59,802
He thought she was
charming and amusing.

31
00:01:59,873 --> 00:02:03,707
Clarice Starling
and Hannibal Lecter...

32
00:02:03,777 --> 00:02:06,678
became friendly?

33
00:02:06,746 --> 00:02:10,682
Inside a kind
of formal structure, yes.

34
00:02:10,750 --> 00:02:13,981
And he was fond of her?

35
00:02:18,758 --> 00:02:19,952
Thank you, Barney.

36
00:02:20,026 --> 00:02:22,017
Thank you very much
for your candor.

37
00:02:22,095 --> 00:02:25,394
And keep all those
wonderful items...

38
00:02:25,465 --> 00:02:28,127
from your personal Lecter
treasure trove coming.

39
00:02:28,201 --> 00:02:30,066
I've enjoyed them immensely.

40
00:02:30,136 --> 00:02:31,865
Mr. Verger.

41
00:02:31,938 --> 00:02:33,030
I almost forgot.

42
00:02:33,106 --> 00:02:35,597
I might be able
to get a cookie down.

43
00:02:35,675 --> 00:02:37,404
What do you say, Cordell?

44
00:02:37,477 --> 00:02:40,446
I think it would kill you.

45
00:02:48,488 --> 00:02:49,614
How much?

46
00:02:49,689 --> 00:02:51,350
250...

47
00:02:51,424 --> 00:02:53,085
thousand.

48
00:02:53,159 --> 00:02:54,888
Cordell...

49
00:02:54,961 --> 00:02:59,193
cut a check for $250,000.

50
00:04:53,246 --> 00:04:55,510
How can she sleep
at a time like this?

51
00:04:56,783 --> 00:04:58,512
She was on a jump-out squad
all night.

52
00:04:58,585 --> 00:04:59,984
She's saving her strength.

53
00:05:26,613 --> 00:05:28,103
No problem, sir.

54
00:05:30,450 --> 00:05:33,351
We got some guy named Bolton
from the D.C. Police.

55
00:05:34,554 --> 00:05:36,488
All right, everyone,
pay attention.

56
00:05:36,556 --> 00:05:37,784
Here's the layout.

57
00:05:37,857 --> 00:05:40,325
Excuse me.
I'm Officer Bolton, D.C. Police.

58
00:05:40,393 --> 00:05:42,861
I see that from your badge.
How do you do?

59
00:05:42,929 --> 00:05:44,453
I'm in charge here.

60
00:05:44,530 --> 00:05:46,725
Officer Bolton,
I'm Special Agent Starling.

61
00:05:46,799 --> 00:05:48,960
So we don't get off
on the wrong foot...

62
00:05:49,035 --> 00:05:51,333
Iet me explain why
we're all here.

63
00:05:51,404 --> 00:05:53,634
I'm here
because I know Evelda Drumgo.

64
00:05:53,706 --> 00:05:55,435
I've arrested her twice
on RICO warrants.

65
00:05:55,508 --> 00:05:58,409
DEA and ATF,
in addition to backing me up...

66
00:05:58,478 --> 00:06:00,241
are here for the drugs
and the weapons.

67
00:06:00,313 --> 00:06:03,441
You're here because our mayor
wants to appear tough on drugs--

68
00:06:03,516 --> 00:06:05,643
especially after his own
cocaine conviction--

69
00:06:05,718 --> 00:06:08,414
and hopes he can accomplish that
by having you join us today.

70
00:06:08,488 --> 00:06:10,649
You got a smart mouth, lady.

71
00:06:10,723 --> 00:06:12,384
Officer, if you wouldn't mind...

72
00:06:12,458 --> 00:06:15,120
I'd appreciate it
if you'd let me continue.

73
00:06:16,262 --> 00:06:18,423
All right, take a look.

74
00:06:18,498 --> 00:06:21,467
Fish market--
back's on the water.

75
00:06:21,534 --> 00:06:23,866
Across the street, ground floor,
is the meth lab.

76
00:06:23,936 --> 00:06:26,336
Evelda Drumgo is HIV positive.

77
00:06:26,406 --> 00:06:29,898
She will spit and bite
if she's cornered, so watch it.

78
00:06:29,976 --> 00:06:32,740
If you happen to be the one
who puts her in a patrol car...

79
00:06:32,812 --> 00:06:34,439
in front of the news cameras,
Officer Bolton...

80
00:06:34,514 --> 00:06:35,947
you don't want
to push her head down.

81
00:06:36,015 --> 00:06:38,176
She'll likely have a needle
in her hair.

82
00:06:38,251 --> 00:06:41,152
We want to take her inside,
not out in the street.

83
00:06:41,220 --> 00:06:42,778
We can get closest with the van.

84
00:06:42,855 --> 00:06:44,152
If it looks good,
on my signal...

85
00:06:44,223 --> 00:06:46,191
we hit the front,
DEA hits the back...

86
00:06:46,259 --> 00:06:48,318
D.C.P.D. backing them up.

87
00:06:48,394 --> 00:06:50,726
She'll have her watchers out
at least three blocks around.

88
00:06:50,797 --> 00:06:52,526
They've tipped her before
in time...

89
00:06:52,598 --> 00:06:55,066
so let's not make spectacles
of ourselves.

90
00:07:06,512 --> 00:07:09,743
-Pretty busy today.
-I agree.

91
00:07:15,688 --> 00:07:18,350
Can I please get
a cup of coffee?

92
00:07:35,041 --> 00:07:37,339
-Did you see that?
-That's a roger.

93
00:07:46,252 --> 00:07:47,549
What's up, man?

94
00:07:57,530 --> 00:07:58,895
God damn it. It's her--

95
00:07:58,965 --> 00:08:01,399
with three guys.
They're all packing.

96
00:08:01,467 --> 00:08:03,059
She's carrying something.

97
00:08:03,136 --> 00:08:04,228
She's got a baby.

98
00:08:04,303 --> 00:08:07,739
Hey, Brigham,
it's too crowded.

99
00:08:07,807 --> 00:08:09,274
There are too many people.

100
00:08:09,342 --> 00:08:11,310
I say we call it off.
What do you say?

101
00:08:11,377 --> 00:08:13,402
I agree.

102
00:08:13,479 --> 00:08:15,845
All units, stand down.

103
00:08:15,915 --> 00:08:18,145
-Whiskey Team copies.
-Burke copy.

104
00:08:18,217 --> 00:08:20,082
This is Bolton. Stay on target.

105
00:08:20,153 --> 00:08:22,883
I said all units stand down,
Bolton, right now.

106
00:08:22,955 --> 00:08:25,082
-Too late. We're moving in.
-Bolton, it's off.

107
00:08:25,158 --> 00:08:26,921
Stand down now.

108
00:08:26,993 --> 00:08:29,587
She's carrying a baby.

109
00:08:29,662 --> 00:08:31,027
All units stand down.

110
00:08:31,097 --> 00:08:32,428
Keep that gun down, Bolton.

111
00:08:32,498 --> 00:08:34,432
Dude got a piece.
Light his ass up.

112
00:08:34,500 --> 00:08:36,161
It's a go. FBl!

113
00:09:19,512 --> 00:09:21,104
Hold it!

114
00:09:21,180 --> 00:09:23,205
Hold your fire!

115
00:09:25,184 --> 00:09:26,549
Don't!

116
00:09:29,622 --> 00:09:32,056
Evelda, get out of the car!

117
00:09:33,960 --> 00:09:35,552
Starling, is that you?

118
00:09:36,996 --> 00:09:39,829
Step away from the car!

119
00:09:41,467 --> 00:09:43,526
Show me your hands, Evelda.

120
00:09:45,204 --> 00:09:46,831
Please...

121
00:09:46,906 --> 00:09:48,305
show me your hands.

122
00:09:48,374 --> 00:09:49,966
How have you been?

123
00:09:50,042 --> 00:09:51,771
Don't do this.

124
00:09:51,844 --> 00:09:52,936
Do what?

125
00:10:25,211 --> 00:10:27,509
It's all right. It's OK.

126
00:10:28,548 --> 00:10:29,640
I know, I know.

127
00:10:29,715 --> 00:10:33,082
Baby, I know. It's OK.

128
00:10:57,343 --> 00:10:59,709
Friends, family, and co-workers
gathered here this morning...

129
00:10:59,779 --> 00:11:01,371
at Arlington
National Cemetery...

130
00:11:01,447 --> 00:11:03,915
to bury BATF agent
John Brigham...

131
00:11:03,983 --> 00:11:05,848
shot and killed
in the line of duty Friday.

132
00:11:05,918 --> 00:11:07,249
He was forty years old.

133
00:11:07,320 --> 00:11:10,812
This ill-fated drug raid that
claimed his life and 5 others...

134
00:11:10,890 --> 00:11:13,688
is the latest in a seemingly
endless series of incidents...

135
00:11:13,759 --> 00:11:15,090
beginning with Waco, Texas...

136
00:11:15,161 --> 00:11:17,686
in which the Justice Department
and the FBl...

137
00:11:17,763 --> 00:11:20,459
have been questioned
about their use of firepower...

138
00:11:20,533 --> 00:11:21,727
rather than judgment.

139
00:11:21,801 --> 00:11:24,395
This time, it was FBI Special
Agent Clarice Starling...

140
00:11:24,470 --> 00:11:26,165
heading up the calamitous
strike force.

141
00:11:26,238 --> 00:11:29,571
Starling attained some measure
of celebrity ten years ago...

142
00:11:29,642 --> 00:11:31,371
when she was given
information...

143
00:11:31,444 --> 00:11:33,412
by Dr. Hannibal
"the Cannibal" Lecter...

144
00:11:33,479 --> 00:11:35,447
which led to the rescue
of Catherine Martin...

145
00:11:35,514 --> 00:11:37,948
daughter of the former
U.S. senator from Tennessee.

146
00:11:38,017 --> 00:11:40,383
However, when she returns
to work later this week...

147
00:11:40,453 --> 00:11:41,977
she won't be so celebrated.

148
00:11:42,054 --> 00:11:43,316
Attorney Telford Higgins...

149
00:11:43,389 --> 00:11:45,050
representing one of the families
of those slain...

150
00:11:45,124 --> 00:11:47,115
says he will file
a wrongful death suit.

151
00:12:02,742 --> 00:12:03,674
Yes, sir.

152
00:12:03,743 --> 00:12:06,234
Get me the Justice Department.

153
00:12:13,552 --> 00:12:15,349
Agent Starling?

154
00:12:15,421 --> 00:12:17,048
This is John Eldridge from DEA.

155
00:12:17,123 --> 00:12:19,148
Assistant Director Noonan,
of course, you know.

156
00:12:19,225 --> 00:12:22,388
Larkin Wayne from our Office
of Professional Responsibility.

157
00:12:22,461 --> 00:12:24,486
Bob Sneed, ATF.

158
00:12:24,563 --> 00:12:26,724
Benny Holcombe,
assistant to the mayor...

159
00:12:26,799 --> 00:12:28,926
and Paul Krendler.
You know Paul.

160
00:12:29,001 --> 00:12:30,336
Paul's come over from Justice
unofficially as a favor to us.

161
00:12:30,336 --> 00:12:32,827
Paul's come over from Justice
unofficially as a favor to us.

162
00:12:32,905 --> 00:12:35,499
In other words,
he's here, and he's not here.

163
00:12:37,743 --> 00:12:41,474
You've seen the coverage
in the papers and on television?

164
00:12:41,547 --> 00:12:44,141
I have nothing to do
with the news, Mr. Krendler.

165
00:12:44,216 --> 00:12:47,083
The woman had a baby
in her arms.

166
00:12:47,153 --> 00:12:48,643
There are pictures.

167
00:12:48,721 --> 00:12:50,120
You can see the problem,
I would think.

168
00:12:50,189 --> 00:12:51,486
Not in her arms.

169
00:12:51,557 --> 00:12:53,582
In a carrier across her chest.

170
00:12:53,659 --> 00:12:55,752
In her arms, she had a MAC-10.

171
00:12:55,828 --> 00:12:58,922
Look, we're here to help you,
Starling.

172
00:12:58,998 --> 00:13:02,024
It's going to be harder to do
with a combative attitude.

173
00:13:07,106 --> 00:13:09,074
Can I speak freely,
Mr. Pearsall?

174
00:13:11,343 --> 00:13:12,435
Your agency
called this office...

175
00:13:12,511 --> 00:13:14,445
to get me assigned to help you
on this raid.

176
00:13:14,513 --> 00:13:16,481
I tried to do that.

177
00:13:16,549 --> 00:13:19,746
I clearly expressed my judgment
and was ignored...

178
00:13:19,819 --> 00:13:22,754
and now a good agent and friend
is dead.

179
00:13:25,858 --> 00:13:28,418
You shot and killed five people
out there, Agent Starling.

180
00:13:28,494 --> 00:13:30,724
Is that how you define
good judgment?

181
00:13:30,796 --> 00:13:33,788
This raid was an ugly mess.

182
00:13:33,866 --> 00:13:37,097
I ended up in a position where
I had a choice of dying...

183
00:13:37,169 --> 00:13:39,069
or shooting a woman
carrying a child.

184
00:13:39,138 --> 00:13:41,800
I chose.

185
00:13:41,874 --> 00:13:43,171
I shot her.

186
00:13:43,242 --> 00:13:46,769
I killed a mother
holding her child...

187
00:13:48,814 --> 00:13:51,180
And I regret it.
I resent myself for it.

188
00:13:51,250 --> 00:13:53,946
Gentlemen, I'm going to
halt this meeting...

189
00:13:54,019 --> 00:13:56,283
and get back to you
individually by phone.

190
00:14:00,626 --> 00:14:02,651
Waste of time.

191
00:14:04,563 --> 00:14:06,724
You have a secret admirer,
Starling.

192
00:14:06,799 --> 00:14:11,463
Isn't much to look at, but he
has friends in high places.

193
00:14:11,537 --> 00:14:14,404
Remember Mason Verger?

194
00:14:14,473 --> 00:14:17,033
Lecter's fourth victim--

195
00:14:17,109 --> 00:14:18,576
the rich one.

196
00:14:18,644 --> 00:14:21,112
The only one that survived.

197
00:14:22,481 --> 00:14:24,881
He has new Lecter information.
He'll only share it with you.

198
00:14:24,950 --> 00:14:26,474
What do you mean,
only share it with me?

199
00:14:26,552 --> 00:14:28,577
You want it, seize it.

200
00:14:28,654 --> 00:14:30,246
We'd rather not.

201
00:14:30,322 --> 00:14:31,846
I wasn't speaking to you,
Mr. Krendler.

202
00:14:31,924 --> 00:14:34,449
When I speak to you,
I'll look at you.

203
00:14:35,861 --> 00:14:37,624
Why would we rather not?

204
00:14:37,696 --> 00:14:38,856
The last time he called...

205
00:14:38,931 --> 00:14:42,389
was when we took Lecter
off the Ten Most Wanted List.

206
00:14:42,468 --> 00:14:44,959
He was upset about that.
We said, "Hey, that's life."

207
00:14:45,037 --> 00:14:48,370
He said, "Hey, this is
a senate oversight committee...

208
00:14:48,440 --> 00:14:50,067
"to make your life miserable."

209
00:14:50,142 --> 00:14:51,803
His family's
political contributions...

210
00:14:51,877 --> 00:14:54,903
may not be enough
to buy a senator...

211
00:14:54,980 --> 00:14:57,005
but they are enough to rent them
from time to time.

212
00:14:57,082 --> 00:14:58,811
There's no reason to go
through that again...

213
00:14:58,884 --> 00:15:02,320
if he really does have
something new.

214
00:15:03,522 --> 00:15:06,286
It's a good deal for you,
Starling.

215
00:15:06,358 --> 00:15:07,552
You can't pretend it isn't.

216
00:15:08,894 --> 00:15:10,919
You get to go back
on a celebrated case.

217
00:15:10,996 --> 00:15:14,591
I'll take care of the media
for your Drumgo killing.

218
00:15:14,667 --> 00:15:15,827
Everyone's going to be happy.

219
00:15:15,901 --> 00:15:18,461
I'm not happy.

220
00:15:18,537 --> 00:15:22,906
Well, maybe you're
incapable of being happy.

221
00:15:22,975 --> 00:15:23,942
Mr. Krendler...

222
00:15:24,009 --> 00:15:26,534
when you're out
on the street...

223
00:15:26,612 --> 00:15:28,978
you know you might take
a bullet in the line of duty.

224
00:15:29,048 --> 00:15:31,209
You accept it, or you get out.

225
00:15:31,283 --> 00:15:33,046
You live with it.

226
00:15:33,118 --> 00:15:35,985
What you don't
expect or accept...

227
00:15:36,055 --> 00:15:38,649
is taking one in the back
in your boss' office...

228
00:15:38,724 --> 00:15:40,851
for doing your job
exactly as they've taught you.

229
00:15:40,926 --> 00:15:42,621
That makes you unhappy.

230
00:15:42,695 --> 00:15:45,186
Of course,
you're right, Starling...

231
00:15:46,265 --> 00:15:48,165
but it doesn't really
change anything.

232
00:15:48,234 --> 00:15:51,465
It changes everything.
It changes me.

233
00:16:42,855 --> 00:16:45,619
I'm Cordell Doemling,
Mr. Verger's private physician.

234
00:16:45,691 --> 00:16:46,919
How do you do?

235
00:16:46,992 --> 00:16:48,687
If you'd be so kind
as to park down at the end.

236
00:16:55,167 --> 00:16:58,603
One's eyes adjust
to the darkness.

237
00:17:02,808 --> 00:17:05,936
Six to eight
versus an estimate of sixteen.

238
00:17:06,011 --> 00:17:07,706
Dylan, they're saying sales
have slowed down.

239
00:17:07,780 --> 00:17:08,940
Seems like
a recurring theme here.

240
00:17:09,014 --> 00:17:11,983
Perhaps corporate spending
on a slowdown.

241
00:17:14,086 --> 00:17:17,283
Mr. Verger,
Agent Starling is here.

242
00:17:17,356 --> 00:17:19,324
Good morning, Mr. Verger.

243
00:17:20,392 --> 00:17:23,850
-Was that a Mustang I heard?
-Yes, it was.

244
00:17:23,929 --> 00:17:25,590
A five liter?

245
00:17:27,700 --> 00:17:28,860
Fast.

246
00:17:30,102 --> 00:17:32,627
Cordell,
I think you can leave us now.

247
00:17:32,705 --> 00:17:37,301
I thought I might stay.
Perhaps I could be useful.

248
00:17:37,376 --> 00:17:41,403
You could be useful
seeing about my lunch.

249
00:17:45,317 --> 00:17:47,217
I'd like to attach
this microphone...

250
00:17:47,286 --> 00:17:49,811
to your clothing or your pillow,
if you're comfortable with that.

251
00:17:49,888 --> 00:17:51,719
By all means.

252
00:17:56,895 --> 00:17:58,863
Here.
This should make it easier.

253
00:18:06,638 --> 00:18:10,904
You know, I thank God
for what happened.

254
00:18:10,976 --> 00:18:13,274
It was my salvation.

255
00:18:14,613 --> 00:18:17,912
Have you accepted Jesus,
Agent Starling?

256
00:18:17,983 --> 00:18:19,473
Do you have faith?

257
00:18:19,551 --> 00:18:20,779
I was raised Lutheran.

258
00:18:20,853 --> 00:18:23,253
That's not what I asked.

259
00:18:23,322 --> 00:18:24,789
This is Special Agent
Clarice Starling...

260
00:18:24,857 --> 00:18:26,722
5-1-4-3-6-9-0...

261
00:18:26,792 --> 00:18:29,522
deposing Mason R. Verger
on March 20, sworn and attested.

262
00:18:29,595 --> 00:18:31,062
I want to tell you
about summer camp.

263
00:18:31,130 --> 00:18:33,360
-It was a wonderful childhood--
-We can get to that later.

264
00:18:33,432 --> 00:18:36,663
We can get to it now.

265
00:18:36,735 --> 00:18:38,669
It all comes to bear.

266
00:18:38,737 --> 00:18:43,299
It was a Christian camp
my father founded...

267
00:18:43,375 --> 00:18:47,971
for poor, unfortunate,
castoff little boys and girls...

268
00:18:48,047 --> 00:18:50,845
who would do anything
for a candy bar.

269
00:18:50,916 --> 00:18:53,077
Mr. Verger, I don't need to know
about the sex offenses.

270
00:18:53,152 --> 00:18:54,676
It's all right.

271
00:18:54,753 --> 00:18:56,983
I have immunity
from the U.S. Attorney...

272
00:18:57,056 --> 00:19:02,221
and I have immunity
from the Risen Jesus.

273
00:19:02,294 --> 00:19:04,819
And nobody beats the Riz.

274
00:19:04,897 --> 00:19:06,797
Had you ever seen Dr. Lecter...

275
00:19:06,865 --> 00:19:08,890
before the court assigned you
to him for therapy?

276
00:19:08,967 --> 00:19:10,229
What do you mean?

277
00:19:10,302 --> 00:19:12,167
Socially?

278
00:19:13,906 --> 00:19:14,930
That is what I mean.

279
00:19:15,007 --> 00:19:16,941
Yes, if you don't mind
talking about it.

280
00:19:17,009 --> 00:19:20,001
-Not at all. I'm not ashamed.
-I didn't say you should be.

281
00:19:20,079 --> 00:19:24,539
No. We met conventionally--
as doctor and patient.

282
00:19:24,616 --> 00:19:26,345
How did he end up at your house?

283
00:19:26,418 --> 00:19:29,353
I invited him, of course.

284
00:19:30,556 --> 00:19:32,615
To my pied-à-terre.

285
00:19:32,691 --> 00:19:37,424
I came to the door in my nicest
"come hither" outfit.

286
00:19:37,496 --> 00:19:42,900
I was concerned
he'd be afraid of me...

287
00:19:42,968 --> 00:19:46,426
but he didn't seem to be
afraid of me.

288
00:19:47,806 --> 00:19:49,706
That's almost funny now.

289
00:19:51,176 --> 00:19:53,235
I showed him my toys--

290
00:19:53,312 --> 00:19:56,076
my noose setup,
among other things.

291
00:19:56,148 --> 00:20:00,414
It's a way you sort of
hang yourself, but not really.

292
00:20:00,486 --> 00:20:02,613
It feels good while you...

293
00:20:02,688 --> 00:20:04,383
Well, you know.

294
00:20:05,757 --> 00:20:09,454
Anyway, he said, "Mason..."

295
00:20:09,528 --> 00:20:11,553
Mason, would you like a popper?

296
00:20:11,630 --> 00:20:14,030
And I said, "Would l?"

297
00:20:14,099 --> 00:20:16,033
And, wow...

298
00:20:16,101 --> 00:20:18,797
once that kicked in,
I was flying.

299
00:20:18,871 --> 00:20:20,304
He said, "Mason...

300
00:20:20,372 --> 00:20:22,772
"show me how you smile...

301
00:20:22,841 --> 00:20:25,275
"to gain the confidence
of a child."

302
00:20:26,512 --> 00:20:29,481
When I smiled...

303
00:20:29,548 --> 00:20:32,483
he said, "I see how you do it."

304
00:20:32,551 --> 00:20:37,284
The good doctor approached me
with a piece of broken mirror.

305
00:20:37,356 --> 00:20:38,482
"Try this."

306
00:20:39,725 --> 00:20:41,454
Try peeling off your face.

307
00:20:41,527 --> 00:20:45,019
"And feeding it to the dogs."

308
00:20:54,306 --> 00:20:56,035
I can still see it.

309
00:20:57,376 --> 00:20:58,343
Try again.

310
00:20:59,478 --> 00:21:00,604
No, I'm afraid not.

311
00:21:02,314 --> 00:21:04,714
That's entertainment

312
00:21:07,052 --> 00:21:10,579
It seemed like a good idea
at the time.

313
00:21:10,656 --> 00:21:12,487
Mr. Verger,
you indicated to me...

314
00:21:12,558 --> 00:21:15,686
that you'd received
some new information.

315
00:21:34,012 --> 00:21:35,309
Where did this come from?

316
00:21:36,448 --> 00:21:39,576
Buenos Aires.
I received it two weeks ago.

317
00:21:41,520 --> 00:21:43,010
Where is the package it came in?

318
00:21:43,088 --> 00:21:45,113
Good question.

319
00:21:45,190 --> 00:21:47,488
There was nothing written on it
of interest.

320
00:21:47,559 --> 00:21:49,550
Cordell, did we throw it out?

321
00:21:50,629 --> 00:21:52,426
I'm afraid we did.

322
00:21:52,497 --> 00:21:53,759
Oh, dear.

323
00:21:53,832 --> 00:21:55,663
You think it'll help?

324
00:21:55,734 --> 00:21:57,895
I hope so.

325
00:21:57,970 --> 00:21:59,665
I hope it'll help you
catch him...

326
00:21:59,738 --> 00:22:04,607
to help cleanse the stigma
of your recent dishonor.

327
00:22:04,676 --> 00:22:06,007
Thank you.
I think that's all I need.

328
00:22:06,078 --> 00:22:09,411
Did you find some rapport
with Dr. Lecter...

329
00:22:09,481 --> 00:22:13,144
in your talks at the asylum?

330
00:22:13,218 --> 00:22:16,187
I know I did
while I was peeling.

331
00:22:16,255 --> 00:22:19,452
We exchanged information
in a civil way.

332
00:22:19,524 --> 00:22:21,890
But always through the glass?

333
00:22:33,872 --> 00:22:35,169
Isn't it funny?

334
00:22:35,240 --> 00:22:37,834
What's that?

335
00:22:37,909 --> 00:22:39,774
You can look at my face...

336
00:22:41,213 --> 00:22:45,775
but you shied
when I said the name of God.

337
00:23:10,509 --> 00:23:11,771
Finding what you want?

338
00:23:11,843 --> 00:23:14,209
Are you sure this is all of it?

339
00:23:14,279 --> 00:23:16,679
That's all there is now.
There was more...

340
00:23:16,748 --> 00:23:21,082
but it's been picked over
little by little over the years.

341
00:23:21,153 --> 00:23:24,748
This stuff's worth lots of money
in certain circles.

342
00:23:26,458 --> 00:23:28,653
It's kind of like the cocaine
that disappears around here...

343
00:23:28,727 --> 00:23:30,194
Iittle by little.

344
00:23:55,187 --> 00:23:57,121
Let me go!

345
00:24:54,880 --> 00:24:56,643
Hey, Barney.

346
00:24:56,715 --> 00:24:59,047
Remember me?

347
00:24:59,117 --> 00:25:01,381
Would you agree for the record,
Agent Starling...

348
00:25:01,453 --> 00:25:03,318
that I've not been
read my rights?

349
00:25:07,659 --> 00:25:09,524
I have not Mirandized Barney.

350
00:25:09,594 --> 00:25:12,324
He is unaware of his rights.

351
00:25:14,032 --> 00:25:16,500
When you turned Dr. Lecter over
to the Tennessee Police--

352
00:25:16,568 --> 00:25:20,561
They weren't civil to him,
and they're all dead now.

353
00:25:20,639 --> 00:25:23,039
They only survived
his company three days.

354
00:25:23,108 --> 00:25:26,043
You survived him six years
at the asylum.

355
00:25:26,111 --> 00:25:29,171
How'd you do that?
It wasn't just being civil.

356
00:25:29,247 --> 00:25:32,011
Yes, it was.

357
00:25:32,083 --> 00:25:35,348
You ever think after he escaped
he might come after you?

358
00:25:35,420 --> 00:25:38,253
He once told me
that whenever feasible...

359
00:25:38,323 --> 00:25:41,087
