he called them.

361
00:25:44,229 --> 00:25:47,130
What about you? You ever think
he might come after you?

362
00:25:47,199 --> 00:25:48,632
You ever think about him at all?

363
00:25:48,700 --> 00:25:50,793
At least thirty seconds
of every day.

364
00:25:50,869 --> 00:25:52,302
I can't help it.

365
00:25:52,370 --> 00:25:56,306
He's always with me,
like a bad habit.

366
00:25:56,374 --> 00:25:58,774
Do you know what happened
to his stuff?

367
00:25:58,844 --> 00:26:00,368
His books, papers, drawings--

368
00:26:00,445 --> 00:26:03,141
Everything got thrown away
when the place closed--

369
00:26:03,215 --> 00:26:04,807
cutbacks.

370
00:26:04,883 --> 00:26:06,373
Barney, I just found out...

371
00:26:06,451 --> 00:26:08,646
that Dr. Lecter's signed copy
of "The Joy of Cooking"...

372
00:26:08,720 --> 00:26:12,349
was sold to a private collector
for $16,000.

373
00:26:13,658 --> 00:26:15,626
It was probably a fake.

374
00:26:15,694 --> 00:26:17,423
The seller's affidavit
of ownership...

375
00:26:17,496 --> 00:26:19,862
was signed Karen Phlox.

376
00:26:19,931 --> 00:26:23,298
Do you know Karen Phlox?
You should.

377
00:26:23,368 --> 00:26:24,926
She filled out
your employment application...

378
00:26:25,003 --> 00:26:27,062
only at the bottom,
she signed it "Barney."

379
00:26:27,138 --> 00:26:30,630
Same thing on your tax returns.

380
00:26:33,278 --> 00:26:35,109
You want the book?

381
00:26:35,180 --> 00:26:37,114
Maybe I can get it back.

382
00:26:37,182 --> 00:26:39,412
I want the X-ray they shot
after you broke Lecter's arm...

383
00:26:39,484 --> 00:26:41,782
during the attack on that nurse.

384
00:26:41,853 --> 00:26:43,844
And everything else you got.

385
00:26:47,893 --> 00:26:51,659
We used to talk about
a lot of things at night.

386
00:26:51,730 --> 00:26:54,722
After the screaming
finally died down...

387
00:26:58,203 --> 00:27:01,138
We talked about you sometimes.

388
00:27:01,206 --> 00:27:02,605
You want to know what he said?

389
00:27:02,674 --> 00:27:04,938
Go get the X-ray.

390
00:27:11,116 --> 00:27:14,517
-I'm not a bad guy.
-I didn't say you were.

391
00:27:14,586 --> 00:27:17,146
Dr. Chilton was a bad guy.

392
00:27:17,222 --> 00:27:18,519
After your first visit...

393
00:27:18,590 --> 00:27:21,889
he started taping
your conversations with Lecter.

394
00:27:24,095 --> 00:27:26,996
These...are valuable.

395
00:27:31,369 --> 00:27:33,166
Go on, now.

396
00:27:34,205 --> 00:27:36,173
You've grieved long enough.

397
00:27:39,945 --> 00:27:41,913
And what'd he say?

398
00:27:43,214 --> 00:27:44,977
What'd he say about me
late at night?

399
00:27:46,217 --> 00:27:49,186
He was talking about inherited,
hard-wired behavior.

400
00:27:49,254 --> 00:27:52,223
He used genetics
in roller pigeons as an example.

401
00:27:52,290 --> 00:27:54,224
They fly way up in the air...

402
00:27:54,292 --> 00:27:57,022
roll backwards in a display,
falling toward the ground.

403
00:27:57,095 --> 00:28:00,622
There are shallow rollers,
and there are deep rollers.

404
00:28:00,699 --> 00:28:02,564
You can't breed
two deep rollers...

405
00:28:02,634 --> 00:28:06,092
or their young, their offspring,
will roll all the way down...

406
00:28:06,171 --> 00:28:08,366
hit and die.

407
00:28:08,440 --> 00:28:11,466
Agent Starling
is a deep roller, Barney.

408
00:28:11,543 --> 00:28:15,070
Let us hope
one of her parents was not.

409
00:28:15,146 --> 00:28:17,205
Surely,
the odd confluence of events...

410
00:28:17,282 --> 00:28:19,944
hasn't escaped you, Clarice.

411
00:28:20,018 --> 00:28:23,146
Jack Crawford dangles you
in front of me...

412
00:28:23,221 --> 00:28:25,951
then I give you a bit of help.

413
00:28:26,024 --> 00:28:28,117
Do you think it's because
I like to look at you...

414
00:28:28,193 --> 00:28:32,493
and imagine how good
you would taste...

415
00:28:32,564 --> 00:28:34,657
Clarice?

416
00:28:34,733 --> 00:28:39,432
I don't know. Is it?

417
00:28:39,504 --> 00:28:42,769
I've been in this room
for eight years now, Clarice.

418
00:28:42,841 --> 00:28:46,937
I know they will never, ever
let me out while I'm alive.

419
00:28:47,012 --> 00:28:49,344
What I want is a view.

420
00:28:49,414 --> 00:28:53,145
I want a window where I can see
a tree...or even water.

421
00:28:53,218 --> 00:28:55,015
I want to be
in a Federal institution...

422
00:28:55,086 --> 00:28:56,121
far away from Dr. Chilton.

423
00:28:56,121 --> 00:28:56,780
