433
00:29:39,464 --> 00:29:41,159
I think not.

434
00:29:41,232 --> 00:29:44,030
What if he came upon a note
in the Capponi Library...

435
00:29:44,102 --> 00:29:46,866
say from Guido de Cavalcanti?

436
00:29:46,938 --> 00:29:48,735
Would he recognize that?

437
00:29:48,807 --> 00:29:50,775
I think not.

438
00:29:50,842 --> 00:29:52,639
They're still arguing.

439
00:29:52,711 --> 00:29:56,010
The Capponi Correspondence
goes back to the 13th Century.

440
00:29:56,081 --> 00:29:58,572
Sogliato wants the job
for his nephew.

441
00:29:58,650 --> 00:30:00,277
But the scholars
seem satisfied...

442
00:30:00,351 --> 00:30:02,251
with the temporary guy
they appointed.

443
00:30:03,455 --> 00:30:05,855
If he's such
an expert on Dante...

444
00:30:05,924 --> 00:30:08,586
Iet him lecture on Dante
to the Studiolo.

445
00:30:08,660 --> 00:30:10,525
Let him face them if he can.

446
00:30:10,595 --> 00:30:13,723
I look forward to it.
Let's set a date.

447
00:30:13,798 --> 00:30:16,631
Very well. On the 14th.

448
00:30:33,384 --> 00:30:36,182
Dr. Fell?

449
00:30:36,254 --> 00:30:39,155
Chief lnspector Rinaldo Pazzi
of the Questura.

450
00:30:39,224 --> 00:30:42,819
Commendatore.
How can I be of service?

451
00:30:42,894 --> 00:30:45,988
I'm sorry. I'm investigating
the disappearance...

452
00:30:46,064 --> 00:30:48,089
of your predecessor...

453
00:30:48,166 --> 00:30:50,657
Signore de Bonaventura.
I was wondering if--

454
00:30:50,735 --> 00:30:53,033
"Predecessor" implies
I have the job.

455
00:30:53,104 --> 00:30:55,095
Unfortunately, I don't. Not yet.

456
00:30:55,173 --> 00:30:56,765
Though I am hopeful.

457
00:30:56,841 --> 00:30:59,309
They are letting me
look after the library.

458
00:30:59,377 --> 00:31:00,708
For a stipend.

459
00:31:02,514 --> 00:31:04,414
The officers
who first checked...

460
00:31:04,482 --> 00:31:08,384
didn't find any sort
of farewell or suicide note.

461
00:31:08,453 --> 00:31:10,387
I was wondering if you--

462
00:31:10,455 --> 00:31:12,753
If I come across anything
in the Capponi Library...

463
00:31:12,824 --> 00:31:16,089
stuffed in a drawer or book...
I'll call you at once.

464
00:31:18,196 --> 00:31:20,130
Thank you.

465
00:31:21,332 --> 00:31:22,993
You've been reassigned.

466
00:31:26,137 --> 00:31:27,229
Pardon?

467
00:31:27,305 --> 00:31:30,741
You were on the Il Mostro case,
I'm sure I read.

468
00:31:30,809 --> 00:31:31,741
Yes, that's right.

469
00:31:31,810 --> 00:31:33,141
Now you're on this.

470
00:31:33,211 --> 00:31:36,203
This is much less grand a case,
I would think.

471
00:31:36,281 --> 00:31:39,978
Well, if I thought of my work
in those terms...

472
00:31:40,051 --> 00:31:41,643
yes, I guess I'd agree.

473
00:31:41,719 --> 00:31:43,550
A missing person.

474
00:31:43,621 --> 00:31:44,815
Sorry?

475
00:31:44,889 --> 00:31:47,517
