in situ, on an object.

705
00:49:39,129 --> 00:49:41,859
Once the print has been
positively identified...

706
00:49:41,932 --> 00:49:44,526
the balance of the money
will be placed in escrow...

707
00:49:44,601 --> 00:49:46,193
at Geneve Credit Suisse...

708
00:49:46,270 --> 00:49:47,760
and may be viewed at any time...

709
00:49:47,838 --> 00:49:50,966
subject to 24-hour
prior notification.

710
00:49:51,041 --> 00:49:53,737
To repeat the message
in French, press two.

711
00:49:53,810 --> 00:49:55,437
In Spanish, press three.

712
00:49:55,512 --> 00:49:56,570
In German--

713
00:50:22,406 --> 00:50:23,532
Buon giorno.

714
00:50:23,607 --> 00:50:26,235
Dr. Fell? It's lnspector Pazzi.

715
00:50:26,310 --> 00:50:28,835
Yes, I can see you.

716
00:50:28,912 --> 00:50:30,470
Come on up.

717
00:51:22,666 --> 00:51:24,224
Snap.

718
00:51:24,301 --> 00:51:27,896
I should have encouraged you
to bring someone along.

719
00:51:27,971 --> 00:51:30,303
The cases, I'm afraid,
are on the heavy side.

720
00:51:30,374 --> 00:51:32,843
Maybe you could
help me with them.

721
00:51:34,011 --> 00:51:35,979
Just down the stairs, I mean.

722
00:51:38,648 --> 00:51:41,208
Yeah. This way.

723
00:51:43,387 --> 00:51:45,287
Here we are.

724
00:51:49,259 --> 00:51:50,726
Is that the inventory?

725
00:51:54,131 --> 00:51:55,894
May I see it?

726
00:51:55,966 --> 00:51:57,126
Of course.

727
00:52:06,743 --> 00:52:09,678
You are a Pazzi of the...

728
00:52:09,746 --> 00:52:11,907
Pazzi family, I think.

729
00:52:13,250 --> 00:52:17,653
Wasn't it at the Palazzo Vecchio
your ancestor was hanged?

730
00:52:17,721 --> 00:52:19,313
Francesco de Pazzi?

731
00:52:19,389 --> 00:52:20,981
Yes, thrown naked...

732
00:52:21,058 --> 00:52:24,027
with a noose around his neck
from a window...

733
00:52:24,094 --> 00:52:26,654
writhing and kicking
alongside the archbishop...

734
00:52:26,730 --> 00:52:29,494
against the cold stone wall.

735
00:52:29,566 --> 00:52:33,832
In fact, I found a very nice
rendering of it here in the...

736
00:52:33,904 --> 00:52:35,735
Iibrary the other day.

737
00:52:35,806 --> 00:52:38,001
If you like, perhaps I could...

738
00:52:38,075 --> 00:52:39,770
sneak it out for you.

739
00:52:39,843 --> 00:52:43,574
I would think that might
jeopardize your chances...

740
00:52:43,647 --> 00:52:46,810
for permanent appointment
to the curatorship.

741
00:52:46,883 --> 00:52:49,044
Only if you told.

742
00:52:50,187 --> 00:52:53,213
Remind me, what was his crime?

743
00:52:53,290 --> 00:52:56,191
He was accused of killing
Giuliano de Medici.

744
00:52:56,259 --> 00:52:57,487
Unjustly?

745
00:52:57,561 --> 00:53:01,258
No. I don't think so.

746
00:53:01,331 --> 00:53:04,357
Then he wasn't just accused.
He did it, he was guilty.

747
00:53:04,434 --> 00:53:06,493
I think that would make
living in Florence...

748
00:53:06,570 --> 00:53:10,472
with the name Pazzi
uncomfortable...

749
00:53:10,540 --> 00:53:12,030
even 500 years later.

750
00:53:12,109 --> 00:53:15,340
Not really.

751
00:53:15,412 --> 00:53:18,040
In fact, I can't remember
the last time...

752
00:53:18,115 --> 00:53:22,552
before today...
someone brought it up.

753
00:53:30,494 --> 00:53:34,055
People don't always tell you
what they're thinking.

754
00:53:34,131 --> 00:53:36,292
They just see to it you don't...

755
00:53:36,366 --> 00:53:39,631
advance in life.

756
00:53:42,706 --> 00:53:46,142
I'm sorry, Commendatore.

757
00:53:46,209 --> 00:53:48,700
I too often say
what I'm thinking.

758
00:53:50,280 --> 00:53:52,578
I'll be right back to help you.

759
00:54:07,030 --> 00:54:12,229
The room you're standing in
was built in the 15th Century.

760
00:54:12,302 --> 00:54:13,428
It's beautiful.

761
00:54:14,938 --> 00:54:16,803
Yes, it is.

762
00:54:16,873 --> 00:54:19,706
Unfortunately I think
the heating system...

763
00:54:19,776 --> 00:54:21,767
was installed
about the same time.

764
00:54:23,246 --> 00:54:25,874
That's a pity.

765
00:54:29,553 --> 00:54:32,750
Okey-dokey,
let's drag these down.

766
00:54:32,822 --> 00:54:35,586
They must be as heavy as bodies.

767
00:55:05,789 --> 00:55:07,222
And the set?

768
00:55:07,290 --> 00:55:08,450
Eight thousand.

769
00:55:12,295 --> 00:55:14,729
-How much is this?
-50,000.

770
00:55:14,798 --> 00:55:16,129
I'll take it.

771
00:55:37,220 --> 00:55:38,710
Scusi, signor.

772
00:55:39,923 --> 00:55:41,220
Well done.

773
00:55:44,127 --> 00:55:46,096
Gnocco.

774
00:55:49,399 --> 00:55:53,961
When you go for his wallet,
he'll catch you by the wrist.

775
00:55:54,037 --> 00:55:56,096
I have done this a few times,
lnspector.

776
00:55:56,172 --> 00:55:57,833
Not like this.

777
00:55:59,009 --> 00:56:02,604
If there isn't a clean print
on the bracelet...

778
00:56:02,679 --> 00:56:07,116
you'll spend the summer
in a cell at the Collicciano.

779
00:56:08,351 --> 00:56:11,115
Give me the bracelet.

780
00:56:11,187 --> 00:56:13,382
Wash your fucking hands.

781
00:56:23,266 --> 00:56:24,756
He's coming.

782
00:57:13,116 --> 00:57:14,310
Grazie.

783
00:58:14,811 --> 00:58:15,778
I got it.

784
00:58:21,851 --> 00:58:24,649
He grabbed me just right.

785
00:58:27,891 --> 00:58:30,485
Tried to hit me in the balls.

786
00:58:34,431 --> 00:58:35,921
But he missed.

787
00:58:40,703 --> 00:58:43,263
Let me help you.

788
00:58:43,339 --> 00:58:45,330
No. Don't.

789
00:59:42,265 --> 00:59:44,096
Sixteen point match, Mr. Verger.

790
00:59:46,269 --> 00:59:47,702
Bingo.

791
01:00:05,388 --> 01:00:06,377
Pronto.

792
01:00:06,456 --> 01:00:07,855
Carlo?

793
01:00:07,924 --> 01:00:08,856
Mason?

794
01:00:08,925 --> 01:00:11,291
Ciao, bello. Come stai?

795
01:00:11,361 --> 01:00:13,886
Very well. Well.

796
01:00:13,963 --> 01:00:16,090
Am I coming to see you?

797
01:00:16,165 --> 01:00:17,962
Yes. Soon, I hope.

798
01:00:18,034 --> 01:00:19,433
But...

799
01:00:19,502 --> 01:00:21,766
first, I need you
to pack off the boys.

800
01:00:21,838 --> 01:00:23,829
-Now?
-Yes, I know.

801
01:00:23,907 --> 01:00:26,705
The day you never thought
would arrive has.

802
01:00:26,776 --> 01:00:29,336
Cordell will fax
the veterinary forms...

803
01:00:29,412 --> 01:00:32,609
directly to Animal
and Plant Health...

804
01:00:32,682 --> 01:00:36,778
but you need to get the vet
affidavits from Sardinia.

805
01:00:36,853 --> 01:00:38,377
Va bene?

806
01:00:38,454 --> 01:00:40,251
Bene, bene.

807
01:00:40,323 --> 01:00:42,018
How are they?

808
01:00:42,091 --> 01:00:44,491
They are big, Mason--
very big.

809
01:00:44,561 --> 01:00:46,085
Tommaso.

810
01:00:51,434 --> 01:00:52,366
Say again?

811
01:00:52,435 --> 01:00:55,529
They are big, Mason--
really big.

812
01:00:55,605 --> 01:00:58,369
Maybe 270 kilos.

813
01:01:00,977 --> 01:01:02,604
Can you hear?

814
01:01:04,981 --> 01:01:06,039
Hear!

815
01:01:14,290 --> 01:01:17,157
They sound fantastic.

816
01:01:27,103 --> 01:01:28,468
Super.

817
01:02:03,606 --> 01:02:04,903
The full balance of the money...

818
01:02:04,974 --> 01:02:08,569
is payable upon receipt
of the doctor alive.

819
01:02:08,645 --> 01:02:11,443
Of course, you won't have
to seize him yourself...

820
01:02:11,514 --> 01:02:13,243
rather just point him out.

821
01:02:13,316 --> 01:02:15,978
In fact, it's preferable
to all concerned...

822
01:02:16,052 --> 01:02:18,247
if that's the extent
of your involvement...

823
01:02:18,321 --> 01:02:19,982
from this point.

824
01:02:20,056 --> 01:02:24,186
I prefer to stay involved--
to make sure things go right.

825
01:02:24,260 --> 01:02:26,194
Professionals will see to that.

826
01:02:28,197 --> 01:02:29,960
I am a professional.
